---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "cmd+kit | Getting Started";
const description = "Install cmd+kit, understand the workspace, and start integrating the package.";
---

<BaseLayout description={description} title={title}>
  <main class="site-shell docs-shell" id="main-content" tabindex="-1">
    <article class="docs-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Docs</p>
      <h1>Getting Started</h1>
      <p>
        `cmd+kit` is split into a framework-agnostic core and framework adapters. React is the
        most mature public adapter today, with Vue and Preact already available as parallel
        integrations. The web app in this repository is the landing page and live configurator.
      </p>

      <h2>Workspace</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>`packages/core`: headless engine and public core types</li>
        <li>`packages/react`: default React UI and bindings</li>
        <li>`packages/vue`: default Vue UI and composable bindings</li>
        <li>`packages/preact`: Preact bindings aligned with the React-facing API</li>
        <li>`apps/example-vanilla`: framework-free verification of the core in the browser</li>
        <li>`apps/web`: Astro marketing site and React playground</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Install by adapter</h2>
      <pre class="code-block"><code>npm install @cmd-kit/react react react-dom
npm install @cmd-kit/vue vue
npm install @cmd-kit/preact preact</code></pre>

      <h2>Headless core</h2>
      <p>
        If you want to render your own UI in plain browser code or another framework adapter, start
        from `@cmd-kit/core` and build on top of the snapshot and execution primitives.
      </p>
      <pre class="code-block"><code>npm install @cmd-kit/core</code></pre>

      <h2>Pick your entry point</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/docs/react">React</a>: best-supported adapter today</li>
        <li><a href="/docs/vue">Vue</a>: slot-based adapter using the same core model</li>
        <li><a href="/docs/preact">Preact</a>: lean runtime with an API close to React</li>
        <li><a href="/docs/astro">Astro</a>: recommended composition pattern for static docs and islands</li>
        <li>`@cmd-kit/core`: framework-free path for custom UI adapters and vanilla browser usage</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Quality checks</h2>
      <pre class="code-block"><code>npm run test
npm run typecheck
npm run build</code></pre>

      <h2>Next steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start with the React adapter if you want the most mature path today. Use Vue or Preact
        when you want the same core behavior in a different component runtime. The homepage
        playground exports React, CSS variables, Tailwind-oriented snippets, and a portable JSON
        config today.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
